      "content": "i mean, sure, history is complicated, but at least originalists are trying to stick to the actual words written down. when judges use the 'living constitution' thing to justify new rights or change old ones, doesn't that basically turn the court into a political body rather than a legal one? it seems like one is a legitimate legal method and the other is just politics by another name.",
